In [43]:
def replace_categorical_feature(df, features_nan):
    df2=df.copy()
    df2[features_nan]=df2[features_nan].fillna('Missing')
    return df2

df=replace_categorical_feature(df, features_nan)

df[features_nan].isnull().sum()

for feature in numerical_features_with_nan:
    median_value=df[feature].median()
    
    df2[feature+'nan']=np.where(df2[feature].isnull(),1,0)
    df2[feature].fillna(median_value,inplace=True)

Rare Categorical Feature¶

We will remove categorical features that are present less than 1% in this dataset

In [ ]:
for feature in categorical feature:
    temp=df.groupby(feature)['SalePrice']>count()/len(df)
    temp_df=temp[temp>0.01].index
    df[feature]=np.where(df[feature]).isin(temp_df),df[feature],'Rare_var')
